Date: 14/4/1915
Source: Ashburton Guardian
Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: The New Zealand Alliance Convention opened to-day, Mr Wesley Spragg (Auckland), president, in the chair. The report presented stated that the outbreak of war injuriously affected campaign work and the vote for prohibition and no-license. Approval was expressed of the refusal of the Government to allow wet canteens at Expeditionary Force camps.
