Quote: He moved, "That this representative meeting of the New Zealand Alliance draws the attention of the Government to the request made by the Maoris at the congress held at Wellington in 1908, when the principle of local option should be extended to the Native race, and earnestly hopes that the numerous petitions presented by the Maoris to the Prime Minister will be favorably considered."
